Goal Description
Develop a modern, enterprise-grade, and visually stunning frontend UI for the Human Resource Management System (HRMS). The goal is to create a complete, responsive, and interactive prototype demonstrating the capabilities of the HRMS, with realistic mock data, multiple user roles, and advanced features (such as AI insights, recruitment kanban, interactive calendars, and settings management).

We will build the frontend using React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion (for animations) + Recharts/Chart.js (for analytics).

User Review Required
IMPORTANT

Dynamic Role Switcher: To showcase the system's Role-Based Access Control (RBAC), we propose implementing a global role switcher in the dashboard header. This will let you toggle between Super Admin, HR Manager, Department Manager, and Employee views instantly to see the interface, dashboards, and available modules update dynamically.

TIP

State vs Router: For an interactive frontend mockup, using a client-side state router or simple hash router allows us to keep the entire system extremely fast, with zero reload lag, making it feel very premium and responsive.

Open Questions
IMPORTANT

Tailwind CSS Version: Which version of Tailwind CSS should we configure for the project? (e.g., Tailwind CSS v3 or Tailwind CSS v4)?
Chart Library Preference: Do you prefer Recharts (highly responsive and reactive for React) or Chart.js (standard canvas-based) for the data visualizations? We recommend Recharts for clean React integration and smooth transitions.
Next.js vs. Vite (React SPA): The prompt mentions Next.js and Vite. Since we are building the frontend UI first, initializing a Vite + React + TypeScript app is highly recommended for faster compilation and easier static deployment of the prototype. Let us know if you prefer Next.js instead.
